latestIgtvVideos.title: Read You Something: V3
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
In today’s video @beingnomnom goes Being Responsible. I am talking to you about something that’s discussed often but forgotten in practice. My family has played a huge role in imbibing in me the practice of reusing things. In this video, I tell you exactly how they’ve done it. If there is a way you reuse things, let me know in the comments below.

#reuse #recycle #reusereducerecycle #beingnomnom #beingresponsible #responsiblecitizen #saynotosingleuse #igtv #dublin #dublinireland #dublinfoodie #indianfoodbloggers #indianfoodblog

latestIgtvVideos.title: Read You Something: V2
latestIgtvVideos.caption: In today’s video I bring to you a poem titled “Ode to Peanut Butter” written by Matt Forrest Esenwine. On that note, introducing to you @manilife_ peanut butter. They have the deep roasted peanut butter that I absolutely love. You can buy them on their website or at @dunnesstores #peanutbutter #poemonfood #foodpoetry #readyousomething #beingnomnom #sponsoredpost

latestIgtvVideos.title: Read You Something: V1
latestIgtvVideos.caption: With an intention to bring two of my most favourite things together rooted “Reading for you”. Where I bring food and stories together and read them. In the very first IGTV of @beingnomnom , I am reading a food blog for you. The title of the blog is “Food, a Constant Ingredient”... I wrote this back in March 2018 and it’s about how food is a big part of our lives. Enjoy 😊 🌟

latestPosts.caption:
#conclave is a movie that stayed with me for a long time. I kept thinking about power dynamics, acceptance, religion, role of men and women in the world but most importantly food. Food in this movie is not loud. It is the quiet backdrop to everything the story wants to tell you. Please watch this movie and let me know what you think. Available to stream on @amazonprime 

#foodandmovies #moviesaboutfood #moviesthatmatter #beingnomnom #movierecommendation #moviebreakdown #amazonprimevideo

If I had to pick one TV show related to food, it would be COOKED by @michael.pollan on @netflix 

Michael Pollan is an American experimental journalist 
who explores food and cooking with curiosity in this show, documenting his journey to understand why cooking is such an essential part of our lives.

This show delves into so many layers of conversation, challenges the way you think about food and cooking, and it’s highly engaging. Check it out and let me know what you think!

#cooked #michaelpollan #foodbasedcontent #content #contentrecommendation #food #foodtalk #allaboutfood #beingnomnom #fantasticfungi #tvshow #tvshowrecommendation #netflix #netflixshows #docuseries #experimentaljournalism

Last part of the jackfruit series. We’ve gone from fruit to seeds to snacks made from those seeds. I hope you try them all 🥰

#beingnomnom #indiansinlondon #londonblogger #jackfruit #jackfruitrecipes

I managed to find some beautiful Jackfruit in London last week. I saved the seeds from them, dried them in the London sun ☀️ and now it’s ready to become a delicious, healthy and a zero waste snack. Follow along to see how it’s made and for little anecdotes here and there 🫶🏼

#beingnomnom #jackfruit #jackfruitlove #indiansinuk #indiansinlondon #zerowastesnacks #londonindians #tropicalfruit #londonfood #indianfoodinlondon #londonblogger

Don’t sleep on the BBQ “ribs” taco (picture #1) - Smoky, saucy, and packed with flavour - a 10/10 🔥 

They also have Chelada 🍺 that took me back to Mexico 

Have you been yet?

latestPosts.caption:
Jackfruit is a tropical fruit commonly found in South India. It’s one of those fruits where it’s used in its entirety, no waste. Fortunately, it’s also found in London. So please try it if you get your hands on this beauty!
